    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - DRIVETRAIN FAILURE ANALYSIS - TRANSMISSION COMPONENTS -
        SHAFTS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>SHAFTS</title>
        <para>Transmission shafts can twist or fracture when stresses are applied which are greater than the design
            limit. The main causes for this type of failure are:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Improper clutch use.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Starting in the wrong gear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lugging.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Incorrect transmission application.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Bumping the dock while backing.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
